cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of robots and their interaction with humans in environments where humans are not present. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of geometric features in 3D scenes to learn human context. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms (SVM) to learn the spatial affordance map. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to learn the spatial affordance map. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of virtual skeleton models in 3D scenes.
